  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, the constants listed in the beacon chain spec are a combination of constants that will never change, eg: `ZERO_HASH`, and \"constants\" that may change for testing or other purposes, eg: `SHARD_COUNT`.\r\n\r\nIt could be helpful to separate constants from configuration to help implementers determine which variables can be set at compile time vs runtime, how much flexibility to give in editing certain variables, etc.",
